This is angular src folder only. 
In this source we have created two modules for two pages - 1)Login page 2) Tweets search page

To view this app in localhost need to have basic setup as mentioned below  --

1) Node js
2) NPM modules
3) Angular version 8
4) Spectre css framework

How to do basic installation--
1) Node js-
=> Angular requires Node.js version 10.9.0 or later.
To get Node.js, go to nodejs.org.

2) NPM modules
=> To download and install npm packages, you must have an npm package manager.  
It uses the npm client command line interface, which is installed with Node.js by default. 

3) Angular cli
=> Install the Angular CLI globally using below command in command prompt- 
npm install -g @angular/cli

4) Spectre css framework
=> Install with NPM using below command -
npm install spectre.css --save

or download minified version css files and put in the src/assets folder and configure in angular.json file as below-
"styles": [
            "src/styles.scss",
            "src/assets/css/spectre.min.css"
          ],
          
          
